{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba8ad783-f555-4b6b-83c0-ea061b6b8865","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update both base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen rebuild and test:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\ndotnet test   # if you have tests\n```\n\nAlso check for any NuGet packages with explicit `10.x` versions (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and bump those to their `11.x` equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"29bfabf5-30d0-42e2-9a21-6f1a86a6a504","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about version bumping across their project files. I don't need to search any codebase — I can answer directly.\n\nKey changes needed:\n1. `.csproj` — `TargetFramework` from `net10.0` → `net11.0`\n2. `global.json` — SDK version from `10.0.100` → `11.0.100`\n3. `Dockerfile` — base images from `:10.0` → `:11.0`\n\n\nI'll provide a concise, actionable answer with the specific file updates they need to make.","outputTokens":394,"requestId":"2832:1CA5E9:34FDD7:3EB2F2:69EAC9FB"},"id":"f5c5cd0c-6c6c-49cd-b574-de9d688c3a1e","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:40:19.983Z","parentId":"d6b2ef0b-9925-4317-a80e-9b509cf7ea7d"}
